{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"9c9a2e21-7e98-5876-945d-ec18ebfaee62","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 36622481-e31a-4309-b6c2-420de2616086 --><h2>How common is it?</h2><!-- end field 36622481-e31a-4309-b6c2-420de2616086 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 93c4a60e-e52a-4974-8106-0b65f17f988e --><!-- begin field aa4b941b-ca98-4097-91cf-3cb8e6d0898c --><p><strong>The exact incidence and prevalence rates of ulcerative colitis are not known, as detection rates and diagnostic criteria differ between studies </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Burisch, 2013</a>]<strong>.</strong></p><ul><li>Ulcerative colitis is the most common form of inflammatory bowel disease, and the incidence and prevalence of ulcerative colitis is increasing worldwide [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Molodecky, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Burisch, 2013</a>].<ul><li>A retrospective study of patient records of 15 GP practices in NE England (n = 135,723) found the incidence of ulcerative colitis was 13.9 per 100,000 per year in 1990–1994, and the age-sex-adjusted point prevalence was 243.4 people per 100,000 in 1995 [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Rubin, 2000</a>].</li><li>A review article cites incidence estimates for ulcerative colitis that range from 0.9 to 24.3 per 100,000 person-years, and prevalence estimates that range from 2.4–294 cases per 100,000 people in Europe [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Burisch, 2013</a>]. A systematic review of population-based studies found annual incidence rates for ulcerative colitis ranged from 0.6–24.3 per 100,000, and prevalence estimates ranged from 4.9–505 per 100,000 in Europe [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Molodecky, 2012</a>]. Within Europe, the highest incidence and prevalence rates are found in Scandinavia and the UK [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Burisch, 2013</a>].</li><li>The incidence of paediatric-onset ulcerative colitis, which represents about 15–20% of all ulcerative colitis cases, ranges from 1–4 per 100,000 per year in most North American and European regions [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Turner, 2018a</a>].</li><li>The prevalence of ulcerative colitis is estimated at 5–500 per 100,000 worldwide [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Molodecky, 2012</a>].</li></ul></li><li>The peak incidence occurs in late adolescence and early adulthood in the second to fourth decades of life, with a small second peak in the fifth decade [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Molodecky, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Mozdiak, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Rosen, 2015</a>].</li><li>Ulcerative colitis affects males and females at approximately equal rates [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/references/\">Molodecky, 2012</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field aa4b941b-ca98-4097-91cf-3cb8e6d0898c --><!-- end item 93c4a60e-e52a-4974-8106-0b65f17f988e -->","topic":{"id":"34aee656-b482-5065-8656-44c487e4e347","topicId":"6a63bd87-53c1-487d-8426-773cffdb4c43","topicName":"Ulcerative colitis","slug":"ulcerative-colitis","lastRevised":"Last revised in April 2020","chapters":[{"id":"8ec19c69-a796-514b-a267-91bd57a12fe3","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"dc4de3c1-9955-536e-9789-a900261d2189","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"04875f8c-29b3-5d60-8e5c-06930138cfc4","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"04f00df3-2de5-5c61-bb95-25edda5f885b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"12402ddb-2eb9-589e-a1c3-24d50e2538f8","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"2c186889-f3c1-5094-b0ce-0b9a81f46d61","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"36a3da73-b00f-5ee2-bfd9-33293a674904","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"5c86e0bc-3476-59dd-b120-519602968645","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"3ab8e65e-aac9-54a1-abb3-9185c76c6004","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"0efa89a1-51f7-59ff-95ce-94faac48f8a5","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"a2b17331-6cfc-56eb-84c5-433f78f4364c","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"01a70081-193a-5d75-92fb-45f84ee7b317","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"87cfff6e-6028-5fda-aee6-4473268cac77","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"116a07eb-6832-5d49-aa1d-497f7c0684a9","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"fef2143b-1809-58f3-bdf9-0d73710d89ae","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors"},{"id":"9c9a2e21-7e98-5876-945d-ec18ebfaee62","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"